title: List of Canada city name etymologies
data: Named by General Thomas Rosser after the Blue Hills of Brandon , which got their name from Brandon House
Named after nearby Dauphin Lake , which was named by French Canadian explorer Pierre Gaultier de Varennes , sieur de La Vérendrye in 1739 in honour of Louis , Dauphin of France
Named after the character of Josiah Flintabbatey Flonatin in the novel The Sunless City by J. E. Preston Muddock
Named after Alvey Morden , the original owner of the land that the community was established on

The name is derived from the French word portage , which means to carry a canoe overland between waterways . In this case the portage was between the Assiniboine River and Lake Manitoba , over la prairie
Named after Thomas Douglas , 5th Earl of Selkirk , who helped establish the Red River Colony
The city 's name means Stone Brook in German
Named after John F. Thompson , the chairman of Inco Limited . The community was designed as a planned community by the company to house workers for its nearby mining operations
Named after Valentine Winkler , a local politician and business owner
Western Cree word meaning muddy waters
intro: This page lists the etymologies of the names of cities across Canada.
